Subject: TSV/ENST v0.3 - Open executable energy/cost replay for HPC policy evaluation

Hello,

I am sharing an open-source tool for energy-aware HPC policy evaluation: TSV/ENST (Temporal State Vector / Energy-Normalized System Throughput).

Repository: https://github.com/tsvt1/tsv-enst

## What it does

- Ingests power/usage telemetry into a normalized TSV schema
- Computes ENST (work_units / energy_j) across multi-site HPC
- Replays policies (energy caps, thermal limits) with cost impact analysis
- Outputs delta_cost_usd_per_1e9_work_units for policy comparison

## Quick test (< 2 min)

```bash
git clone https://github.com/tsvt1/tsv-enst
cd tsv-enst && npm install
npm run demo:public
```

Outputs:
- leaderboard_real.csv: Site rankings by ENST with cost
- replay_summary_real.json: Policy impact (baseline vs constrained)

## Key metric from demo

delta_cost_usd_per_1e9_work_units: $29.27

This represents the cost delta when applying energy_cap_w=2500 policy.

## Why this matters

- Reproducible: deterministic traces (seed 20241215), SHA256 verified
- Executable: no PDFs, just clone and run
- Compatible with PowerStack / GEOPM ecosystem concepts

